      <section eId="sec_72_440">
        <num>72.440</num>
        <content>
          <p>A coroner may, upon receipt of an affidavit from any person stating that he believes or has reasonable grounds to believe that a person who is dead and buried died from poisoning or other illegal cause, order the body exhumed and a post-mortem examination or autopsy conducted.</p>
